 *   return `GameResult<T>` from their fallible methods. This
 *   tutorial shows how to wire them up.
 * - @ref tutorial_database — The database adapter is the best
 *   example of rich error handling: every query, prepared statement,
 *   and transaction returns `GameResult<T>` with subsystem-specific
 *   error codes.
 * - `advanced/FOUNDATION_ADAPTERS.md` — deep-dive on how the
 *   adapters translate kcenon foundation errors into `GameError`.
 * - `include/cgs/foundation/error_code.hpp` — the authoritative
 *   list of all `ErrorCode` values.
 */
